  "caption": "Read this number twice.\n\n$135,000,000,000.\n\nThat's what Meta plans to spend on AI infrastructure in 2026. Nearly double last year.\n\nNow read this number: 15,000.\n\nThat's how many human jobs could be cut to help pay for it. Up to 20% of Meta's entire workforce.\n\nReality Labs already lost 1,500 positions. Mid level managers, QA teams, customer support, and internal IT are next.\n\nMeta's stock climbed 3% on the layoff news. Wall Street rewarded the cuts.\n\nThis isn't about efficiency. It's about replacement. The largest social media company on Earth is betting that AI infrastructure is worth more than the people who built it.\n\nThe AI gold rush has a human cost. And we're watching it happen in real time.\n\n#Meta #AI #Layoffs #BigTech #FutureOfWork",
